The paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence in real-time strategy games, specifically StarCraft: Brood War. This falls under the category of AI in gaming, which is a subfield of AI. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms such as Monte Carlo Tree Search and Negamax, which are commonly used in game theory and optimization problems, falling under the categories of game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.RO). The paper also presents a library for squad movement planning, which involves coordination and decision-making, falling under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
